Un'esotica grotta è stata scoperta e riservati permessi di pianificazione ti concedono l'opportunità di creare un parco unico in questo particolare habitat! Costruire in superficie è severamente vietato, il numero di visitatori estremamente limitato, per cui è necessario conquistare le profondità per garantire il successo di questa impresa.

Dovrai essere in forma smagliante per affrontare questa situazione! Gli ex proprietari hanno abbandonato questo parco, lasciandolo in condizioni disastrose; bilancio in negativo, un grosso prestito da restituire, layout ridicolo e alcune attrazioni gravemente inefficienti. Invertire le sue sorti sarà un vero e proprio miracolo.

E' tempo di scartare i nostri piani per un parco a tema festivo in questa gioiosa location. Ricorda solo che il denaro a disposizione fa parte di un prestito, non è un regalo! Addobba il tuo paradiso invernale con uno scenario adeguato e attira le allegre folle da ogni dove.

Hai collezionato tutte le Stelle di Bronzo per 'La sfida succulenta di Capitan Manzo'.
Hai collezionato tutte le Stelle d'Argento per 'La sfida succulenta di Capitan Manzo'.

Hai completato ogni obiettivo nella 'Sfida succulenta di Capitan Manzo'!

Il Circuito di Capitan Manzo è stato costruito al posto di un vecchio tracciato sul lungomare per avere i vantaggi del patrimonio locale. Sfortunatamente, durante la costruzione sorsero problemi economici e si dovettero fare dei compromessi. La pista risultante è stata giudicata una delusione dal pubblico. Puoi realizzare il pieno potenziale del sito?

Questo parco ha entusiasmato il pubblico per più di un secolo, ma sta iniziando ad essere oscurato dalle macchine da brivido svettanti e da capogiro dei nuovi parchi. Il consiglio è entusiasta di rinvigorirlo con alcune eccitanti e moderne attrazioni pur preservando le sue radici. Sei pronto alla sfida?

Il Parco in centro doveva portare un po di felicità a questo famigerato quartiere, dove le guardie si sicurezza chiedono salari più alti a causa del rischio aumentato, ma le ambizioni del fondatore furono compromesse dagli alti livelli di crimine. Puoi riuscire dove hanno fallito e portare un po di gioia nell'area?
Unisciti alla Squadra Hotdog di Capitan Manzo e cucina alcuni gustosi parchi.
La Sfida succulenta di Capitan Manzo

Il ristorante di Miss Elly ha delle strutture eccezionali, compreso un grande coaster di legno per un pò di eccitazione! Ma visto che si trova in una località remota non ha molti visitatori e il suo potenziale è inespresso. Riuscirai a costruire in questa zona e attirare le folle?

Hanno girato alcuni film abbastanza famosi qua fuori nel deserto. Assomiglia a Marte, vero? Il posto non è più richiesto – è tutta computer grafica di questi tempi – ma la compagnia non vuole lasciarlo andare. Vogliono invece che tu lo trasformi in un parco a tema!

Un poveraccio ha comprato questa miniera da un cercatore e ha chiesto alcuni grandi prestiti per pagarla. E' venuto fuori che è una truffa. La canaglia aveva salato la miniera! Ora sta cercando di trasformarla in un'attrazione turistica con alcuni fuochi d'artificio e con strade stile Vecchio West, ma non sta andando così bene come sperava e ha bisogno del tuo aiuto.
Devi fare un bel colpaccio per vincere qui. Riesci a domare la frontiera selvaggia?
Montagna Russa Shuttle, che permette al treno di viaggiare in avanti fino ad un punto terminale prima di viaggiare all'indietro lungo il percorso fino alla stazione di partenza.

Una Montagna Russa tradizionale fatta principalmente in legno, il cui risultato è una eccitante, aspra e selvaggia attrazione. Questa variante utilizza una vettura più moderna del coaster in legno 'The Monster'.
Le emozioni di questa particolare Montagna Russa si trovano nelle vetture che ruotano liberamente, insieme a strette e piatte curve che generano alta forza di gravità laterale.
Una Montagna Russa dove il treno è tirato a catena verticalmente prima di essere capovolto e che può passare attraverso la stazione più volte.

Tracciato ufficiale della montagna russa Steel Vengeance di Cedar Point. Pista in acciaio e supporti al coaster in legno si combinano per creare un ibrido che può invertirsi, pur mantenendo l'aspetto e le caratteristiche di una Montagna Russa in legno.
Una Montagna Russa invertita e lanciata che passa avanti e indietro attraverso la stazione più volte, prendendo velocità ad ogni passaggio.

Impostazioni Staff Standard: • I Vantaggi dell'edificio Staff forniscono bonus normali. • Lo staff si licenzia ad un livello felicità normale. • Lo staff inizia con una felicità normale. • Lo staff smette di lavorare al 15% di energia.
Impostazioni Staff Facili: •I Vantaggi dell'edificio Staff hanno un effetto maggiore. • Lo staff si licenzia ad un livello felicità più basso. • Lo staff inizia con una felicità più alta.

Quando gli intrattenitori sono impostati su Apatico:
• Gli intrattenitori non aumentano la felicità dei visitatori come normale. • Gli Intrattenitori divertono meno visitatori alla volta.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Commerciale:
• Gli Intrattenitori non aumentano la felicità dei visitatori come normale. • Gli Intrattenitori divertono più visitatori alla volta.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Predefinito:
• Normale crescita della felicità per i visitatori. • Normale intervallo di tempo fra le performances. • Normale quantità di visitatori per performance. • Normale carico di lavoro prima che gli Intrattenitori diventino stressati. • Normale salario e livelli di energia.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Facile:
• Gli Intrattenitori aumentano la felicità dei visitatori più del normale. • Gli Intrattenitori possono performare più spesso. • Gli Intrattenitori possono sopportare più carico di lavoro. • Gli Intrattenitori non si stancano facilmente.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Energico:
• Gli Intrattenitori perdono energia ad una percentuale di velocità minore.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Titolato:
• Gli Intrattenitori richiedono più denaro per essere felici.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Stanco:
• Gli Intrattenitori perdono energia ad una percentuale di velocità maggiore.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Riconoscente:
• Gli Intrattenitori richiedono meno denaro per essere felici.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Difficile:
• Gli Intrattenitori non aumentano la felicità dei visitatori come normale. • Gli Intrattenitori fanno lunghe pause tra le performances. • Gli Intrattenitori sono oberati di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi. • Gli Intrattenitori si stancano velocemente.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Pigro:
• Gli Intrattenitori non aumentano la felicità dei visitatori come normale. • Gli Intrattenitori fanno pause molto lunghe tra le performances.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Appassionato:
• Gli Intrattenitori aumentano la felicità dei visitatori più del normale. • Gli Intrattenitori divertono più visitatori alla volta.

Quando gli Intrattenitori sono impostati su Stressato:
• Gli Intrattenitori sono oberati di lavoro anche con piccoli carichi di lavoro.
Impostazioni Staff Difficili: • I Vantaggi dell'edificio Staff hanno un effetto ridotto. • Lo staff si licenzia ad un livello felicità più alto. • Lo staff inizia con una felicità più bassa.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Apatico:
• Gli Spazzini sono più lenti a svolgere le mansioni.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Predefinito:
• Normale durata del lavoro. • Normale velocità nel parco. • Normali richieste di salario. • Normali livelli di energia.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Facile:
• I cestini sono più capienti. • Gli Spazzini sono più veloci a svolgere le mansioni. • Gli Spazzini possono sopportare più carico di lavoro. • Gli Spazzini non si stancano facilmente.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Energico:
• Gli Spazzini perdono energia ad una percentuale di velocità minore.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Titolato:
• Gli Spazzini richiedono più denaro per essere felici.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su to Stanco:
• Gli Spazzini perdono energia ad una percentuale di velocità maggiore.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Riconoscente:
• Gli Spazzini richiedono meno denaro per essere felici.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Difficile:
• I cestini hanno una capacità minore. • Gli Spazzini non sono molto veloci a svolgere i compiti. • Gli Spazzini sono oberati di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi. • Gli Spazzini si stancano velocemente.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Pigro:
• Meno efficaci nella pulizia delle toilettes. • Più lenti a svolgere i compiti. • Velocità di movimento rallentata.

Quando gli Spazzini sono impostati su Appassionato:
• Gli spazzini svolgono i compiti più velocemente. • Gli spazzini si muovono per il parco più velocemente.

Quando gli Spazzini sono sono impostati su Stressato:
• Gli Spazzini sono oberati di lavoro anche con piccoli carichi di lavoro.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Apatico:
• I Manutentori non incrementano la durabilità delle attrazioni come normale. • I Manutentori sono più veloci a svolgere le mansioni.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Predefinito:
• Durata Ispezioni/Rinnovi/Riparazioni normale. • Durata miglioramento normale. • Livello prevenzione rotture normale. • Velocità di spostamento per il parco normale. • Paga e livelli energia normali.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Facile:
• Diminuisce soglia di rottura. • I Manutentori sono più veloci a svolgere le mansioni. • I Manutentori si spostano per il parco più velocemente. • I Manutentori possono sopportare più carico di lavoro. • I Manutentori non si stancano facilmente.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Energico:
• I Manutentori perdono energia ad un tasso ridotto.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Titolato:
• I Manutentori richiedono più denaro per essere felici.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su to Stanco:
• I Manutentori perdono energia ad un tasso aumentato.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Riconoscente:
• I Manutentori richiedono meno denaro per essere felici.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Difficile:
• Aumenta soglia di rottura. • I Manutentori non sono così veloci a svolgere le mansioni. • I Manutentori si spostano per il parco più lentamente. • I Manutentori sono oberati di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi. • I Manutentori si stancano velocemente.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Pigro:
• Più lenti a svolgere le mansioni. • Velocità di movimento più bassa.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Appassionato:
• I Manutentori sono più veloci a svolgere le mansioni. • I Manutentori hanno un effetto maggiore sulla durabilità delle attrazioni.

Quando i Manutentori sono impostati su Stressato:
• I Manutentori sono oberati di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi.
Impostazioni Staff in straordinario: • Lo Staff ha bisogno di meno energia per lasciare l'edificio Staff. • Lo Staff smette di lavorare al 1% di energia.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Apatico:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno meno possibilità di rilevare borseggi dalle segnalazioni. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno un raggio di rilevamento dei crimini ridotto.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Guercio:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno un raggio di rilevamento ridotto.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Predefinito
• Possibilità di rilevamento segalazioni normali. • Raggio di rilevamento normale. • Velocità di corsa e di spostamneto per il parco normali. • Normale capacità di sopportare il carico di lavoro. • Richieste di salario e livelli di energia normali.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Facile:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno un raggio di rilevamento dei crimini aumentato. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza sono più veloci quando inseguono. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza possono sopportare più carico di lavoro. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza non si stancano facilmente.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Energico:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza perdono energia ad un tasso ridotto.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Titolato:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza richiedono più denaro per essere felici.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Stanco:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza perdono energia ad un tasso aumentato.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Riconoscente:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza richiedono meno denaro per essere felici.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Difficile:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno un raggio di rilevamento dei crimini ridotto. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza non sono così veloci quando inseguono. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza sono oberate di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza si stancano velocemente.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Pigro:
• Corrono più lentamente. • Velocità di spostamento per il parco ridotta. • Si stancano più velocemente di correre e pattugliare.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Appassionato:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno più possibilità di scovare i criminali dalle segnalazioni. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza hanno un raggio di rilevamento dei crimini aumentato. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza si riprendono dalla corsa più velocemente. • Le Guardie di Sicurezza possono inseguire ad un tasso più elevato.

Quando le Guardie di Sicurezza sono impostate su Stressato:
• Le Guardie di Sicurezza sono oberate di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Predefinito:
• Velocità di servizio normale. • Effetto normale sulla felicità dei Visitatori. • Normale carico di lavoro prima che i Venditori si sentano stressati. • Richieste di salario normali. • Livelli di energia normali.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Facile:
• I Venditori possono sopportare più carico di lavoro. • I Venditori non si stancano facilmente. • I Venditori sono più veloci nel servire i Visitatori.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Energico:
• I Venditori perdono energia ad un tasso ridotto.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Titolato:
• I Venditori richiedono più denaro per essere felici.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Veloce:
• I Venditori servono più velocemente del normale.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Stanco:
• I Venditori perdono energia ad un tasso aumentato.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Riconoscente:
• I Venditori richiedono meno denaro per essere felici.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Difficile:
• I Venditori si stancano facilmente. • I Venditori sono oberati di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi. • I Venditori non sono così veloci a servire i Visitatori.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Pigro:
• Velocità di servizio minore.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Appassionato:
• I Venditori servono i Visitatori velocemente. • I Venditori hanno un effetto positivo incrementato sulla felicità dei Visitatori.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Stressato:
• I Venditori sono oberati di lavoro anche con carichi di lavoro bassi.

Quando i Venditori sono impostati su Automa:
• I Venditori non hanno effetto sulla felicità dei Visitatori. • I Venditori servono i Visitatori velocemente.

Sudditi! Costruite coaster di difficoltà crescente per soddisfare l'appetito di Re Coaster.
Hanno detto che nessuno riuscirebbe a costruire un parco al Burrone Molly. Dimostra che si sbagliano! Attento ai limiti costruttivi di altezza, e finanzia la costruzione di un colossale coaster!

La furia dell'enorme golem è stata finalmente placata, congelata dall'eterna lotta contro i F.I.D.O.. I nostri esperti confermano che la creatura sia inattiva, ma i membri dello staff non sembrano convinti; pretendono un aumento per la loro permanenza! Utilizza la monotoraia per sfruttare al massimo lo spazio a disposizione e crea un parco a tema sci-fi davvero unico.

Secondo alcune voci gli ingegneri del parco avrebbero avuto incontri... spiacevoli, causando la fuga a gambe levate dello staff, e questo ha portato alla sua recente vendita. Il prezzo è un vero affare, per cui assumi del personale, porta a termine la costruzione del parco e ignora eventuali segnalazioni di sinistri rumori provenienti dal sottosuolo. Sono sicuro che non ci sia nulla di cui preoccuparsi...

Uno strano oggetto trovato nel deserto sembra esercitare una strana influenza sulle attrazioni del parco – tutto continua a guastarsi e stiamo terminando le finanze. Assumi alcuni manutentori, organizza i loro turni di lavoro per riparare le attrazioni e mantenerle operative, sconfiggi il potere del Monolito e fai in modo che il parco torni a guadagnare.

Il governo ha recentemente venduto un piccolo tratto di terra ad acquirenti privati, i quali hanno colto al volo la possibilità di investire su un nuovo parco a tema. Poco tempo dopo la grande apertura, la gestione di questo parco a tema sci-fi è misteriosamente scomparsa, insieme a tutti i risultati delle loro ricerche. Porta il parco al successo finanziario, guadagna abbastanza da poterti permettere la ricerca di nuove attrazioni e trasforma questo luogo di stranezze in un clamoroso trionfo.

Gli affiliati di questo futuristico centro dello shopping hanno messo in dubbio il loro impegno a lungo termine dopo i deludenti risultati finanziari. Ottieni e mantieni la loro fiducia ottenendo il maggior profitto possibile dai tuoi negozi e dalle tue strutture. L'organizzazione degli ambienti e la giusta tariffazione saranno le chiavi della svolta, i magnati più astuti sfrutteranno al meglio le insegne pre-costruite per le facciate dei negozi.

Attraccate, ciurma! Ben arrrr...rivato a Planet Coaster! Dai fuoco alle polveri e prendi il controllo di questo esplosivo parco Pirata. Costruisci attrazioni, attira le folle e fai vivere ai visitatori indimenticabili momenti di cappa e spada!

Pietro Gambadilegno, pirata in pensione e neo-imprenditore, si trova in grosse difficoltà. Il suo parco è sommerso di debiti, incompleto, e scarseggia in quanto a divertimento. (Se solo ricordasse dove ha sepolto il suo tesoro... Era qui da qualche parte.) Afferra il timone e inverti la rotta, prima che questa nave si rovesci!

Il Teschio? E' apparso un bel giorno, sorgendo dal terreno in cerca di vendetta... o almeno credo. Si vocifera che sia maledetto, ma tutto quel che so è che rende scontenti i visitatori. Serve il tuo aiuto per contrastare gli effetti del Teschio, altrimenti il parco non si risolleverà. Rendi felici i visitatori e aumentane il numero. Assumi intrattenitori, avvia campagne di marketing, fai tutto ciò che meglio credi per gonfiare le casse.

La famiglia Silversmith sta aprendo un parco a tema sfruttando i terreni di sua proprietà per contrastare l'inarrestabile ascesa dei propri debiti. Il tuo compito sarà quello di creare un parco di successo, lontano dagli abissi della crisi, ma tenendo conto di qualche piccolo accorgimento... I Silversmith sono persone decisamente all'antica e permetteranno la costruzione di sole attrazioni ‘tradizionali’, so you may want to aim your Marketing efforts at families and ensure your ride sequences offer value for money. Oh, dimenticavo... costruisci con attenzione, dato che la proprietà tratterrà una percentuale su eventuali rimborsi... Buona fortuna!

Dicono che questo albero sia il cuore del mondo. Sarai in grado di portare il giusto rispetto a Madre Natura realizzando un parco tematico amico dell'ambiente attorno al maestoso albero, o metterai in vendita il bosco per profitto, spremendo il più possibile questo angolo verde di paradiso?

Posiziona gli oggetti con il cursore prima di inserirli nel parco. Usa la tastiera per attivare la rotazione e i controlli altezza.

Gli Extra per Sentieri possono rendere il tuo parco un posto più bello per i visitatori. Usa il cursore per posizionare gli Extra sopra o lungo gli angoli dei tuoi sentieri, così che i visitatori possano usarli.
Seleziona un oggetto nel parco per vedere il suo pannello informazioni e le opzioni di gestione. Apri i menù in basso allo schermo per iniziare a costruire o vedere più opzioni.

Gli Edifici dello Staff permettono ai membri dello Staff di riposarsi e recuperare energie. Capacità migliorata e vantaggi extra per gli occupanti possono essere acquistati dalle opzioni dell'edificio.
Posiziona lo Staff con il cursore prima di inserirlo nel parco.
Cambia il paesaggio del tuo parco con questi strumenti creativi. Seleziona da una varietà di pennelli per scolpire, dipingere e aggiungere acqua, quindi applica nell'area attorno al cursore.

Resurrect the fortunes of an abandoned and haunted theme park, with the Ghostbusters standing by to eliminate any stubborn spooks in your way. Will a new day dawn for this dilapidated park once the ghosts are gone for good?
The ghosts are fighting back. Try to raise the spirits of your guests while the Ghostbusters stay on top of the spirits in your park.
Ghost activity is now at unprecedented levels. It's the last stand and these spooks are not giving up without a fight. This looks extraordinarily bad...

Take charge of a new theme park featuring a unique Ghostbusters area dedicated to the iconic heroes. Walter Peck of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) is investigating the park following reports of supernatural disturbances in the area.

People are getting agitated and unhappy in the park. Ray and the Ghostbusters will investigate and check for evidence of psychomagnotheric slime flow, but in the meantime, you need to look after the guests.

Slimer has been spotted in the park! No wonder the P.K.E. readings were rising. It’s time to call on the Ghostbusters for help, but this is still a theme park, so take care of the guests who are still turning up.

More ghosts are appearing, so call on the rest of the Ghostbusters to keep the park’s paranormal activity under control. Peck is raising fees and tightening the screws too. And to top it off, it looks like strange things are starting to happen at Spook Central...

Some people think we catch ghosts for fun…
I admit that it has its moments. But also, its rewards. And that’s what we need here. More money.
And are we not the most kick-butt problem solvers the fine people of New York have ever had?
I’ve been looking at the balance sheet and it could use some work.
Bottom line. We need to increase our income. And profits.
Egon’s talking about our finances, Peter. Not our proton packs.
Just tinker with the wires, Egon. Turn up the positrons or whatever.
Administering electroshock negative-reinforcement to naive test subjects?
You know what I like more than anything?
Okay, do you know what I like more than anything except me?
That’s legitimate research, Egon. And a hoot. But no.
Right you are Winston. And bustin’ ghosts. For cash.
...and our proton packs still aren’t what we’d call 'legal'.
Just remember, we want to keep Peck out of our hair...
Good, ‘cause I’m in a streaming state of mind. Proton streaming, that is.
I want to keep him out of my everywhere.
The task before us is a simple one. This park needs a serious reduction in ghosts.
Agreed. We need to capture and contain as many ghosts as possible.
Now, this is why we are here. This park is overrun with ectoplasmic energy.
Gentlemen, and I use that term loosely, we are burning moonlight. Let’s get us some ghosts!
Ray, I don’t want anyone else in my lab.
Time to show the residents of New York generally, and visitors to this theme park specifically, what we do.
I think Ray meant it’s time to go after some ghosts, Egon.
This is just the kind of roller coaster for me. Sensible design, not too fast…
Winston’s right. What it needs is more. Venkman?
Egon, while it might be you, I’m really not sure it’s everyone else...
The ups, the downs, the extreme dips and twists and turns are not enough, apparently.
Sorry, did someone mention the need to add some cool?
Ah. Got it. I mean, how much more could you possibly add to me?
What we need to add is some cool.
Okay, but I don’t like danger.
These attractions are lacking in that certain something. We need to get that adrenaline pumping. Like when we are hunting ghosts…
Neither do I, Egon. I love it. I live for it. We all do. Right?
The best part. That and these cool jumpsuits.
Scares. Thrills. I know, it’s weird. But that’s what this park needs.
I’m just going to assume you have an answer.
It’s like you’ve just described my life. Minus the lawyers.
If we raise the quality of this coaster, then that’s what we’ll get.
The devil is in the details.
I meant if we get the right speed on this coaster, it could pay-off for us.
And last time I checked, also in the containment unit back at HQ.
When was the last time you checked?
I’ve run a number of calculations, and I think I can say with some degree of confidence that if we can get this coaster to the correct speed, then it should be a successful venture.
When you’ve got a proton pack on your back, everything is worth a shot.
Now that’s the can-do attitude I’m talking about.
Hey, if you don’t hit a ghost, you always hit an insurance claim.
With all the fireworks we’ve been making in the park busting ghosts, maybe it’s time for an official show. Fireworks, I mean.
You know the old saying... “why ask for permission now, when we can ask for an inventory of damaged goods later?”
Might cut down on the destruction.
A fireworks display would really liven up this place.
And maybe all the noise and color will have some effect on the ghosts as well.
Yeah, enough of this doom and gloom thing. Let’s burn something. You know, for the kids.
Gozer brought a heck of a light show. Think we can do better?
We need to keep it this way. The paranormal presence in this part of the park appears to be under control. For the moment. Less chaos equals...
...less chances to really mess something up.
How do our spiritual entity stats look?
We need to find that fine line between success and the need to keep us around.
Compared to absolutely anyone else? Amazing.
P.K.E. readings have been steadily going in the right direction.
Egon, how do the numbers look?
But if there are no ghosts, then what are we? The Ghostbusters’ livelihoods depend on the 'dead in the hood'.
I’ve only done that half a dozen times. This year.
We need to raise our guests happiness. Ideas?
You’d think meeting a real-life Ghostbuster would be enough. And Egon lights up the room wherever he goes. Usually as a result of radioactive residue on his clothing...
I’m happy. Are you happy, Winston?
Happy I don’t have to deal with this... heck, yeah.
Smiles and laughter. It means people are happy.
That’s it, Peter. We need to raise people’s spirits. Genius.
Some of our ghosts smile and laugh. Are they happy?
Ghosts are people, Ray. Were people. Raised spirits, if you will.
Yeah, I get it. We need to raise people’s spirits.
I can bring in my collection of spores, molds and fungi. Maybe we can set up an exhibit.
I’m just saying... have you seen the look on a child’s face after they’ve gazed upon their first penicillium digitatum culture?
As much as I’m sure they would love it, I think we should look for some other ways to brighten the guests’ mood.
We need to raise the guests happiness. The question is how?
Have you ever seen the studies of what gets left behind in a hotel room?
If by disgusting, you mean fascinating and intellectually stimulating.
Let’s just focus on getting the hotel up and running.
And at a quality, and price, that meets our expectations.
People need a place to stay.
Let’s hit two ghosts with one stream. We need a new hotel.
And we need a place to tear up.
I’ve run the analytics, and I’m inclined to agree.
Let’s try and drive the overall rating up. Though it might bring in more haunts, specters and spooks.
Then we absolutely have to do it.
This park is good, but I think it could be even better.
I’ve been called socially awkward in group settings.
Let’s work on the park rating. Remember, there’s good... then there’s best.
Then there’s me. And all of us. And Egon.
We’re not a group, we’re a team. Better than the best.
We do have plenty around the park. And it would be something you can’t get anywhere else.
I think all of this interference from Peck, combined with the amount of psychokinetic energy and psychomagnotheric slime found in the park is having an effect on it’s overall rating...
We’ll need raise the rating another way.
Now stay with me here for a moment. Slime-corn. Just let it percolate. Popcorn covered in slime.
You know what you lack, Ray? Vision.
And that’s money they could be spending in the park. On us. We’ve gotta put a stop to it.
People are having their money lifted by pickpockets.
I’m not sure how safe the park is right now. People are losing their valuables to pickpockets.
That’s really not our jam, Egon. Our foes tend to be a little more transparent.
Okay, so we’ll throw some particles around. Egon, do proton packs work on the living?
We still need to put a stop to it.
Phantoms and spirits that need cash? It doesn’t sound right.
I suspect our culprits can be found among the living.
We’re going to need to stay vigilant.
Agreed. This isn’t something you can solve with a proton pack.
Hey Ray, we’ve got a real problem developing in the park with folks’ wallets getting ghosted.
Some of the most beautiful places I’ve ever visited are cemeteries.
Tombstones require a lot of dead people under them.
I’m with Egon. No reason you can’t take in the scenery even if you are throwing down on a ghost.
Or... we could just go with props and save ourselves some headaches with the legal system.
We could get the scenery rating up in the park, especially around the queues.
I have some extra proton packs. Not completely safety checked, mind you.
We need to give the guests something to keep them occupied while they are waiting for a ride.
That’s disappointing. Egon was onto a winner.
No thank you. I’d rather eat a copy of Tobin’s Spirit Guide.
Relax, Ray. I wasn’t thinking of actually doing it. Anymore.
The only thing worse than the paranormal elimination business is the restaurant game. It’s all that dealing with the public.
Still, a new restaurant is a good idea.
Agreed. Nobody likes to catch vacant souls on an empty stomach.
At this point, as long as we have a restaurant that meets our standards, it will do.
We charge them for an empty plate. Eat all you want. Great for dieters and, of course, we are gluten-free. Ghostburgers. Where your burger is a ghost. And tastes as good as you imagine it.
All this ghost bustin’ is making me hungry.
Is it the long hours, the daily interactions with the dead, getting the slime out of your clothing, or maybe it’s the paid medical...
I was just running through a list.
It’s really just free advice from Egon.
Yeah, and I’m good with all that. Seriously. But about that medical...
There is research to support the theory that there is a direct correlation between worker productivity and emotional well-being.
That would have been the Egyptians, Peter.
The park would be running better if it had happier employees.
Maybe the donuts would have got it done faster.
Egon, free donuts on Fridays didn’t build the pyramids.
If we keep the staff happy, we might keep our guests happy as well.
Dial it back, Winston. You’re getting Egon excited.
As a Ghostbuster, the one thing we never do is quit. We have to keep the staff from doing so as well.
What’s our policy on resigning, though?
We need to make sure nobody quits. No matter how adversely the psychomagnotheric slime affects people’s psyches.
Looks like it’s time for a little attitude adjustment.
Ray, you take all the joy out of death.
When I started as a Ghostbuster, I was grateful to have a job. Guess not everyone has that same attitude.
The staff is on edge. Clearly they are afraid of the supernatural nature of the park. We need to keep an eye on the situation.
Peter, there was a time when we all were.
So they’re afraid of some ghosts?

Hey, I followed you out of the library to cover your back. I was simply, uh, running to... to keep up. Plus, I used to have a thing for librarians. The glasses and pulled back hair. Now? Ruined. All ruined.
Thefts are way too high in the park, Ray.
Agreed. We need to get this under control.
Right. The key is them not knowing.
Even if we clear out all the ghosts, people won’t come if they know they are going to get ripped off.
We’ll need to acquire hammers. And nails. They aren’t currently in our ready bags.
If all of these thefts continue, we may need to start nailing things down.
It’s a figure of speech, Egon. We’re not really going to nail things down.
That’s unacceptable. That money should be heading our way.
Ray, people are losing their hard earned cash here…
It’s definitely a problem. We've got to do something about it.

That means your specters, spooks and spirits problems are now in the hands of professionals. Oh, and we'll have Walter Peck and his regulations out of your hair in no time flat. Sorry, I realized I haven't introduced myself. Really, I mean, I shouldn't have to, seeing as you must know the Ghostbusters, but just in case... I'm Ray Stantz, PhD, uh, doctor of parapsychology, with a minor in metallurgy. I'm an expert in paranormal history and have travelled extensively, both in this plane of existence and others. I'm also a non-transient, corporeal entity of the state, county and city of New York... that includes the Five Boroughs, of course. And most importantly for you in this particular situation, I've been dealing with ghosts and other ectoplasmic-generated phantasms for years as a founding member of the Ghostbusters. All this is to say, you now have the best, correction, only, experts with the knowledge and experience to help you deal with your potentially possessed theme park. And if I might say, personally, I can't wait to get started. This is gonna be great.

I see you've already met Walter Peck, which means you must be pretty nervous by now, but as of this moment it's the Ghostbusters who are on the scene, ready to believe you and ready to help. That means your specters, spooks and spirits problems are now in the hands of professionals. My understanding is that you may have run into a little friend of ours we call Slimer. Well, let me reassure you that he's relatively harmless for a Class V full-roaming vapor. Which is to say that he can bring down your whole operation if we don't get him under control. Sorry, I realized I haven't introduced myself. Really, I mean, I shouldn't have to, seeing as you must know the Ghostbusters, but just in case... I'm Ray Stantz, PhD, uh, doctor of parapsychology, with a minor in metallurgy. I'm an expert in paranormal history and have travelled extensively, both in this plane of existence and others. I'm also a non-transient, corporeal entity of the state, county and city of New York... that includes the Five Boroughs, of course. And most importantly for you in this particular situation, I've been dealing with ghosts and other ectoplasmic-generated phantasms for years as a founding member of the Ghostbusters. All this is to say, you now have the best, correction, the only, experts with the knowledge and experience to help you deal with your potentially possessed theme park. And if I might say, personally, I can't wait to get started. This is gonna be great.

Okay, I've had a chance to review the current situation vis-a-vis your park, and frankly, I'm concerned. Based on what I've seen so far, you've got a potential disaster on your hands, and I don't mean from whatever atypical things are happening. Everything is explainable. Given time, we will find the answers. Now, down to business. Based on the reports I've seen, this area of the park shows all the hallmarks of a band of flimflam artists who have been preying on the good, stupid, people of New York for years. This is a confidence game. You are being conned by a group of snake-oil salesmen that call themselves... The Ghostbusters.

So, guests in your park, and even some of your staff, claim to have seen a ghost. Have they? Well, let me put that concern to rest right now... you see, there are no such things as ghosts. My name is Special Agent Walter Peck. And I'm the authority in charge of this investigation. Be assured, the full weight and power of the EPA are now on the case.
Ray Stantz... you and your fellow hoax-ters should be doing dinner theater somewhere and butting out of where you don't belong.
I'm on to you, Stantz. And when the time comes, for you and the rest of your so-called Ghostbusters, I drop the hammer.

My name is Special Agent Walter Peck. And I'm the authority in charge of this investigation. I'm going to start by figuring out how the Ghostbusters pulled off that little trick of theirs with that... that green glob of goo. But be assured, the full weight and power of the EPA are now on the case. I mean, besides the Ghostbusters, who else are you gonna call?
Too late, Peck. The Ghostbusters are already here.
We're following up on an anonymous tip, Peck. Obviously, we could bury the hatchet and work together on this. Ghostbusters and EPA working hand in hand.
I hope it's not on your foot.

So Stantz claims you didn't call the Ghostbusters. Now, while that would normally work in your favor, I'm going to ignore that fact because I need him to sweat a little. That means you will as well. Therefore, all EPA regulations are hereby in effect. I'm imposing fees for our presence, which you will more than gratefully pay for. And if I sense any further disturbances, or any environmental impact from this park, there will be further punishments... uh, payments, imposed.

Now, the call that came into the Ghostbusters office was an anonymous tip. Which doesn't bode well when it comes to tying that to a paying client. Venkman and Egon said this was a fool's errand... well, Venkman did anyway, but do what you love, and the money will find you is my motto. So here's how I see this working. Like any elimination job, it's not just what you see, but what's hiding in the woodwork that matters. I suspect there is a lot more ghost activity happening here than what we have on the surface. So what we'll need to do is lure them out into the open, where the Ghostbusters patented, 'almost licensed by the city of New York', particle thrower can be most effective. I'll provide you with guidance for all things Ghostbusters for this themed area of your park. I'll make suggestions and requests that should make this section of the park more enticing to the spirit world. Talk about scary rides, right? If your park is haunted, we'll know soon enough.
And remember, buster, I'm watching your every move.
Let's start by dealing with some of your personnel issues. Sure, seeing a ghost can make some people... most people, uneasy. And it's cost your park some of its workforce. You need to get staffing.

They say you're good at your job, which means you should be able to handle the extra attention this park is about to receive with some of the modifications we're going to be making. Oh, boy, if they think they are afraid now... just wait. This is AWESOME. We're going to run a theme park... with spirit, and spirits.
Okay, this is progress. With the employee situation squared away, we can look at other areas of the park.
It better not, because last time, your elaborate prank left me covered in melted marshmallow.

I once had a dream of something I loved from my childhood. Something sweet and soft, and oh so full of creamy, pillowy goodness. And then it tried to destroy Manhattan, so I roasted it. The Stay Puft Marshmallow Man. The form of the Destructor. So let's put that misunderstood sailor in the park. And, uh, don't worry... about that other stuff. Based on our extensive, and I do mean, extensive research on inter-dimensional gods - admittedly after the fact - I don't believe sentient, angry and grotesquely over-sized marshmallow men can ever happen again.
Now, that... that I can hope for.
And they say dreams don't come true.

Your park is looking a bit like a graveyard. Which, and don't get me wrong here, I support. But your guests, and my ghosts, like a little action. I'd start looking at building the place up and increasing the appeal of the park, which should draw in more ectoplasmic energy. Then we'll see what's what.
Great job... really great. This place is coming together. And if we like it, and the guests like, then the spirits will too. And then we get busy.

I don't want to brag... but I'm something of a marksman when it comes to the particle thrower. I can hit pretty much everything with it. Which, sometimes, admittedly, can be a problem. I've set my best score on the shooting ride. Care to see if you can beat it? Just remember, you're playing with fire. Okay, more accurately, an unlicensed nuclear accelerator, so, you know, be careful.
You think I'm not onto your tricks, Stantz? Because I am, mister. And this time, I won't fall for them. Or stand for them. Or take them lying down. And I'm not bending over backwards, either.
Hey, you've been working hard and deserve a little down time.
Not bad... not bad at all. And you've managed to leave the building standing. That's actually impressive for a rookie.
Oh, you can be assured that the EPA is looking into this substance.
Or of someone who needs a handkerchief.

Listen, Peck. I don't care if you believe in ghosts or not. Because this place is radiating an intense amount of transdimensional energy, and that is evidenced by the amount of ectoplasmic residue, that's slime to you, we are finding.
This residue is tangible, physical proof of the presence of the supernatural.
This park remains the subject of an environmental probe, regardless of how well it may be doing in other areas.

The Ghostbusters have pulled the wool over the eyes of New Yorkers for far too long, and now it is the EPA that will be taking you to cleaners. Because of me, this racket of yours is soon coming to an end. So you better watch your backside, mister.
I was trying to protect the city.
Ooo, probe! That sounds like harassment.
Doctor. And because of you, an angry god from another dimension, with an admittedly questionable hairstyle, almost turned Manhattan into an apocalyptic, burning hell...
You were trying while the Ghostbusters were crossing the streams and actually doing it.
Putting things over on people is something you think you're good at, isn't it mister?
Ah, it sounds like I'm going to enjoy the afterlife.
Okay, so in spite of what Peck has tried to do... and spite is the operative word here... your park is beginning to look profitable. Maybe a new ride would really put things over the top.
Did you know, Peck, that many ghosts linger in the physical dimensions because they won't let go of their grudges?

Alright, profits are up. This is turning out better than expected. Now, I suspect that the reason that mysterious caller tipped us off in the first place may start coming into play. So we need to be on our toes. Remember, when it comes to ghosts and otherworldly beings, what you can't see is what you need to look for.
We secure the environment at the EPA.
In case you haven't been paying attention, Stantz, I'm not a people person.
I believe the saying is keep your friends close and your enemies closer.

You may have to increase security in the park based on what is happening with the Psycho-Reactive Slime. Security cameras, guards, work rosters... get on top of all of it. Maybe this is a place where Peck could actually be helpful.
That must be one crowded carpool.

Everything suddenly makes so much sense. I think there's something wrong with Peck. I mean, more wrong than usual. The negative energy generated by the psychomagnotheric slime must be having a field day with him.
I kind of like it, myself.
Great. Twice the idiots, half the competency.
There's been a change in the overall energy of the park. Not for the better, I might add.

You would, Peck. You're surrounded in negativity. As I was saying, I've suspected that when the conditions were right, we'd get a spike in phantasmic activity, and with it, an increase in ectoplasm. I've called in Egon to help me investigate what is happening.

Don't listen to him. Nobody else does. I'll deal with the spooks, while you deal with the guests. See if you can restore some calm to the park. Egon and I will check for evidence of psychomagnotheric slime, which can really mess with people's moods.
It seems you've got a handle on chilling out the guests. Which is good, 'cause I think this may just be the calm before the storm.

For a while, I was thinking of opening up a diner... an eatery, what have you... called Gutbusters. Build on the brand, right? Everyone's gotta eat. Fact is, one of our first big traps was that ugly little spud with an insatiable appetite that you met earlier. So, see what you can come up with... research and build a successful restaurant. Maybe our spirits, like our guests, hunger for something...
Busy wiping up snot while someone else did all the hard work, I see.
No... the Environmental Protection Agency is serious business. You and the Ghostbusters... you're nothing but disaster artists.
I'll have you know, Peck, collecting ectoplasm is serious business.
I see you've elevated your dog and pony show to the next level. Now, you're chasing ghosts around the park, are you?

Oh, I remember. I remember how you and the Ghostbusters conned the city with your Ghostbusters'... uh, Ghostbusters'... bag of deceptions. And I know, Stantz, that includes inducing some kind of hallucinations and mass hysteria. Well, boo-hoo-hoo, you won't scare me this time.

We don't chase. Peck. We track paranormal and ethereal transdimensional entities, then capture them with beams of proton energy, secure them within traps and transfer them to the Ghostbusters' Ecto-Containment Unit. The one you shut down, remember?
I'm not the one you should be afraid of.

My P.K.E. Meter has been pinging like crazy. Then, hey, right on cue, guess who just made an appearance in the park? You remember that ghost I mentioned with the voracious hunger? The ugly green spud? It's a nasty Class V full-roaming vapor we've nicknamed Slimer. And the ghost haunting your park? Well, there you go. This is it. Time to suit up. It's go time.

My P.K.E. Meter has been pinging like crazy. Like, the needle's been buried. Then, hey, right on cue, guess who just made a command appearance in the park? Slimer... that's the nickname we gave it. A Class V full-roaming vapor. And now it's here. But so are the Ghostbusters. This is it. Time to suit up. It's go time.
Good job! The Ghostbusters are kicking butt and taking names.
And the size of your ego.
This is me ignoring you, Stantz. Listen, I know a thing or two about hotels, and luxury sells.

When we first got the firehouse, it was amazing... because we had a place to set up Ghostbusters HQ. But it didn't come without some pain... financially, I mean. Fortunately, we have Louis taking care of the books now. And in addition to his forays into demonic possession, he's really good with real estate. What I've learned is you have to manage the size of your building.
No problem for you there, Peck. Your ego, anyway.
Especially when you can charge it to the government.

Feels like we might need more places for the guests to stay. And more places for the ghosts to haunt. Wait, I've got it. You should build a hotel. Personally, I'm partial to the Sedgewick... they have a very, uh, lively, dining room. I've destroyed worse. But you decide.
No one to squeeze for cash, huh? Not much of a con-man, are you, Stantz?
And your paycheck is an illusion. In that case, all is right with the world.
Those rooms are paying dividends. Which reminds me, I'm still not sure who is paying us. The Ghostbusters took this job on an anonymous tip, so we really don't have a client...
That's what I've been trying to tell you since the beginning. Ghosts are real.
Listen, Peck, if my P.K.E. readings are accurate, you have no idea how wrong you are.

When I was a kid, one of my favorite places was Coney Island. They had a ride... a coaster called the Cyclone. What a place to face your fear. Plus, hot dogs. That's what you need. Not the hot dogs. A new coaster. Not too intense. All this paranormal activity has your guests on edge. Um, and er, it needs that Ghostbusters flair... Man, I could really go for a hot dog.

Things are looking up. That's solid work on your part all around. From what I can see, the new coaster has also increased the overall fear-based adrenaline in the park. That should bring about more intense psychomagnotheric slime activity. Maybe then, we'll see what's really trying to reach out from the other side.

Well, I think we've reached the point where I need to call the rest of the guys in to assist on this project. Egon Spengler and Peter Venkman are both doctors, like myself, and also skilled spirit butt-kickers. And Winston Zeddemore is as good as they come when you need a complete paranormal elimination specialist. Together with myself, you'll have full Ghostbusters protection.
I've about wrapped up this investigation, and will soon issue my report on what has been happening in the park.
Don't think for a moment you can play me, Stantz. There is nothing to fear. The EPA is on site.
If my P.K.E. Meter is right, the fireworks are just about to start.
If our data is correct, the fireworks are just about to start.

That's where you're wrong, Peck. Look, I've faced off against some pretty terrifying baddies over the years and was I scared? Yes. Of course. Pretty much every time. I was also excited. But, in all my time with the Ghostbusters, I've only experienced this level of ectoplasmic energy a couple of times before. Something big is definitely coming.
Egon, Venkman and Winston are working with me to clear the park of as many ectoplasmic entities as possible. Our proton wands are smoking. Do your job and we'll do ours.
And haven't I? The charade is over, Stantz. I have everything I need to shut down the Ghostbusters once and for all.
And you never will be again. Fine, I admit it. I called the Ghostbusters. You got me. Call the cops... oh, wait, I am the cops.
Do it. Do it. See if you bozos ever see a dime.
I, I, uh, I, I, I... it doesn't matter.
Peck saw what was happening in the park and thought we, the Ghostbusters that is, were planting evidence of spiritual activity. His goal was to trap us... catch us at our own game. Right, Peck?
The Ghostbusters are not your problem, Peck. We never have been.
You're a bureaucrat, Peck. And we'll be sending our bill to the EPA.
Let me ask you something, Walter. If you called us, who called you?

I've been thinking... really working through this... and well, I'm wondering if Walter Peck is all he appears to be. He doesn't care how he found himself here at the park? He's not bothered even a little bit by that lack of information? Come to think of it, I haven't seen him recently.
Hey, I'm not saying that you should go all-in on the Ghostbusters themed scenery and merchandise. But you should.
I'm not sure I follow you?
That's preposterous! What help would I possibly need from the Ghostbusters?

This is what the Ghostbusters are all about. Twenty-four-seven, three-hundred sixty-five days a year professional, reasonably-priced, supernatural elimination services for the greater New York region and beyond. And the beyond is where the real excitement can be found, right, Peck?
Incorrect. You've been following us since the beginning, because you're the one who called the Ghostbusters.
I told you that Ghostbusters merchandise would pay off in the long run. So, uh, Venkman would like to know what you are planning to do with the extra cheddar.

Alright, I hope you're ready. The park is primed with ectoplasm and psychokinetic energy. We have a target-rich environment of extreme spiritual turbulence. Whatever's been waiting to go down, that wait is over. I only hope it's not the end of the world again. Because that was a lot of overtime.
Great. It's the end of the world. I knew it. Well, I should have known it. The Traveler. The Destructor. Of course. It was right in front of me the whole time.

Okay, this is bad. Peck is the Keymaster. That means we have to find Zuul, the Gatekeeper. And quick. Otherwise, we get Gozer. And believe me when I say that is one hot mess of a god with severe anger issues. And an interesting sense of fashion.

That Gozer is a real buzz-kill. And by that I mean its buzz can literally kill. It starts by lowering the happiness of everyone nearby. Including your guests. You'd think that a Class VII god, one who's also known as Gozer the Traveler, would find a theme-park... fun. You know, like almost anyone else. Instead, Gozer is radiating negative energy that can put a real damper on everyone's day. And life.

It's Gozer. We're too late. One of the park guests must have been possessed by Zuul, the Gatekeeper. Okay, okay, I've dealt with this god before. Not much of a talker, though. No pressure, just the end of all life as we know it. So, here's the plan. Well, a plan. You keep the park up and running, and me and the guys will deal with your all-powerful, indestructible, omnipotent, immortal god inter-dimensional infestation problem. Because we're the Ghostbusters, and no job is too big.

True story: Even before Peck's 'anonymous' tip-off came into the office, Egon had come to the park with Janine... I know, that in and of itself is cause for concern... and he sensed radiant pyschokinetic energy of abnormally high levels. Confirmed it with his P.K.E. meter. This felt like another round with Gozer, never good. If so, we knew that Zuul and Vinz Clortho would need vessels. Anyway, Peck being a dog... I should have seen some of the signs. Or not ignored them. So that's on me. Maybe. If so, my bad. Whoops.

When it is all said and done, it comes back to your training. And to how little you care for your own well-being. Peck thinks we're stupid, but he hasn't studied and researched the world beyond what we can touch as I have. Sure, it can be frightening and dangerous. But that's what science is supposed to be. Paranormal research isn't about answering questions, it's about questioning answers. If it sounds like I'm trying to rationalize madness, it's because I am. What we need to do is reverse the particle flow generated by our throwers. How? We're gonna cross the streams, which is so not advisable for a number of reasons, the foremost being that if it goes wrong, we could create total protonic reversal. The end of life, reality, even time as we understand it. But what are the chances that will happen? Don't answer that. We gotta get ready.
Ha! Ray Stantz telling the truth? Not likely.
Grrr... grea... okay. Why? What did you do to me?
I'm fine. Though I could use a walk. Or a run. Maybe I'll find a stick.

And that is why you don't mess with the Ghostbusters. We have the tools and the talent. I mean, just how many times do we have to remind this god who it is up against? And, we even saved Peck, though that wasn't a top priority. Or middle one. Really, kinda bottom of the list, truth be told.

Things look stable for now. P.K.E. readings are within acceptable limits. However, this place, the park, is still hot with ectoplasmic potential, so tread carefully. The spirit world never goes away, it just sort of retreats. And waits. And Gozer... Gozer is always a threat, so don't let your guard down.

She handles like a beauty, huh? I did most of the work on her myself. 6.3-liter V-8 with some custom mods. And those tail fins... You know, not many people ever get to drive the Ecto-1, so consider yourself fortunate.
Oh, I almost forgot. I've left you the keys to the Ecto-1. Don't scratch the paint, cadet, or I'll be the one haunting you.
The EPA is not something you fool with lightly. Costs are going up.
When you conspire with the Ghostbusters... well, that comes at a cost, buddy. To your sanity, perhaps. But to your bottom line, most definitely.
You should be grateful your helping the environment by paying your fees. Some people choose to do good... I'm referring to myself, obviously... and some are forced to.

Don't think you can put one over on me. Hmm. Tell you what, I'll put it in story form. Fact. The EPA will get its money. Fiction. The Ghostbusters will catch some ghosts. The end. By Walter Peck. I think it could be a best-seller.
I'm on you every step of the way. Don't think you won't pay a price.

Because of, or more than likely, in spite of the Ghostbusters help, you seem to be handling your park with some success. Well, we'll soon see about that. The EPA is raising its fees. Care to complain?
I hope you don't think I'm treating you unfairly by raising the EPA fees. Actually, I don't care.
Lay down with dogs and you're gonna get fleas. Stand up with the Ghostbusters and your gonna get fees. Increased, that is. I thought of that myself, by the way. One of my many talents.

You feel that? That is the power of the federal government coming down on you in the “true form of the destructor.” Me. Walter Peck. And I don't bring a light show and mirrors. I bring rules and regulations. And, a bill marked “payment due.”
The cost of business is going up. The EPA, which in this case means me, is raising its, my, fees.
This is their confidence game, you understand. This is how the Ghostbusters fool the masses. Please. There is no Gozer. There is only Zuul. As a friend of mine used to say.

Something strange is happening. I mean, stranger than usual when we are talking about the Ghostbusters. For example, I know Gozer is just an elaborate hoax, yet, I have this dogged feeling about this so-called god's return.
Gozer? Pft, right... I've seen this Ghostbusters con before.
Then you should know it's real.
New Yorkers are natural builders. Like the song... “If you can make it there, you can make it anywhere.” But you, make it there. Your park, I mean.

This place looks a little barren. I'm used to the city where we pack 'em in like sardines. Maybe you should think about adding some more attractions to your park. Make it feel more like home, you know?
I'm really liking what you're doing with the place, but honestly, it could be, you know, more. Buildings, rides... more fun. More fear. More stuff. You know what to do... hopefully.
This is the place I'd like to come to... a Ghostbusters Theme Park. Come on, I mean, it's cool, right? But it'd be even cooler with a few improvements here and there.
Hey, I'm not going to tell you how to do your job, but you should try to take this park to the next level with a few improvements.
As a fellow business owner, I'd advise you to find ways to make a profit. The goal is to bust ghosts, not yourself.
No. Don't listen to him. The Ghostbusters are up to their old tricks. It's always slight of hand with them. Deception. Then, then... they get you.
No. Don't listen to him. The Ghostbusters are up to their old tricks. It's always slight of hand with them. Deception. Then, then... they get you.
Hmmm... is that so? I suppose that next you'll warn us that one is going to become sentient, grow to a hundred times its size, and wiggle down Fifth Avenue eating everything in its path.
Where there's room for failure, there's also room for improvement. And jello. There's always room for jello.
Where there's room for failure, there's also room for improvement.
Don't be ridiculous, Peck. That only happens with marshmallow men. As far as I know. So you should be very careful about putting ideas in my head.
I need you to start acting like a Ghostbuster. We never acknowledge defeat. We don't give up. We don't know how to. And we can't afford to, either.
Don't take this the wrong way, but a focused, non-terminal repeating phantasm could do a better job than you are.
I thought you had this... you do have this?

I just realized that you may be wondering about the proceeds from the shooting ride. It's a bustin' good time, right? The kids love it. And, the parents... they hate that the kids love it. Thing is, if you know about crossing the streams, you know that causes a reverse particle flow... sort of like the profits for the ride. Venkman insisted that we make our fees somewhere in this deal, and so that particular ride is... well, that's Ghostbusters money. I'm sure whether you do or not, you understand.

Have we talked about that ride that seems to be siphoning off the fees to someplace beyond your control? No? Good, it's probably for the best. For you, and for the Ghostbusters. I mean, Venkmen... he insisted we make something somehow somewhere on this deal.
This is great. I knew you could do it. Well, I suspected you could. Hoped you could, anyway. I never had a doubt... that I shared with anyone. How 'bout we leave it at that?
That's the spirit. No... I mean, that's literally the spirit. But we'll tag 'em soon enough.
Go ahead, take this challenge on. It changes nothing. And gives me more to add to your file.
So, you and the Ghostbusters are at it again!
Finally, you are beginning to understand me.
So much anger, Peck. You're like psychomagnotheric slime, but with less personality.
Why not just give up and admit you're a loser? Hmm... Yes. That's why you fit in so well with the Ghostbusters.
If you think ghosts are your problem, then you really haven't been paying attention, buster.
Parapsychologists? Snake oil salesmen is more like it. And you're teaming up with them? There are already enough Ghostbusters in the world causing headaches.
Ugh. I see you're falling for the whole Ghostbusters scam.
This really has that Ghostbusters feeling.
You're pretty good at this. Say, have you ever considered a permanent future in paranormal elimination?
We make a heck of team.
All you have to do is start breaking a lot of things, and setting them on fire, and I'd swear you are a real Ghostbuster.
I want those Containment Units off-line right now, and I want it done in the name of the EPA.
I'm shutting the Ghostbusters down. Those phoney Containment Units are going off-line.
That's it. I think we've had just about enough of this silliness. I'm shutting the Ghostbusters down.
These ridiculous Containment Units are doing nothing but furthering the Ghostbusters shell-game. I'm taking them off-line.
Oh, I remember, mister. I remember how you and the Ghostbusters created some sort of shared delusion and mass hysteria. Well, maybe you can fool the common man, but you can't fool me.
No one makes mistakes like I can.
What are you doing, Peck? You know what happened last time you shutdown our Containment Unit.
You'll be letting out the ghosts. That would be a mistake.

That Containment Grid of yours is untested, unlicensed, unproven and unsafe. And, apparently unsecure as well as my understanding is that one of your unliving has escaped. I hope I'm communicating how unhappy the EPA is over this situation.

I think the Ghostbusters call it Slimer. I call it an abomination. And it's loose in your park. Needless to say, this is not acceptable. Clean up your mess before the EPA does, because if we do it, you won't like it. I, however, will.
That pet of yours is an environmental nightmare.
Do I? Let me warn you, Stantz, if that... that thing, is free in the park...
So, we may have a bit of a problem. That little green gob of uninhibited, overly-caffeinated, aggression has escaped.
I'd prefer not to. Especially to you.
You got the nightmare part right, at least.
We have everything under control, Peck. Things are my speciality.

I don't want you to think this is weird or anything, but I've been keeping an eye on you. Think of it as an evaluation. I'm good at judging people. So, I wanted to let you know I think it's time for you to step up.
Best way to learn is on the job experience. Also, it's the best way to die.
Let's do this. What could go wrong? No, I'm legitimately asking.
I hope you're ready, because here it comes.
I love this town... and this theme park.
I'm ready to believe in you.
They didn't stand a ghost of chance. See what I did there?
Oh, boy. This is bad. The Gargoyles have turned into Terror Dogs. That means Zuul and Vinz Clortho - a couple of really heinous spooks themselves - are already here.
Looks like the Terror Dogs are missing. Believe me when I say these bad boys have a bite worse than their bark. We'd better find 'em.

The Terror Dogs are back, and judging by their appearance, it looks man's best friend just became humanity's worst enemy. In Peck's case, this isn't much of a change, but, and I can't over emphasize this “but”, where the Gatekeeper and the Keymaster go, Gozer is sure to follow.
I haven't seen this before. I'll get the Proton Pack ready, just in case.
Ooo... new stuff. I like stuff.
You got a new high score!
That's a new high score. Good job!

If you thought you'd seen the last of me, you couldn't be more wrong. The EPA is not to be trifled with, my Ghostbusters-conspiring friend. Walter Peck has his eye on you, and don't you forget it. Just because I'm not here, don't think that I'm not here. Because I'm not. Am.

Okay, you've proven you're up to a challenge. Ghostbusters material, even. So, how'd you like to put those skills to work managing a new park? It's gonna be harder. But you know who to call if you get in trouble. The Ghostbusters... in case that wasn't clear.

I've thrown the book at you, and yet you come back for more. Have it your way. I'll give you the win if it means you stop wasting the EPA's valuable time. And whatever Stantz told you happened... remember, he can hypnotize you into believing anything. He once convinced me he was actually human.

Well, this is unexpected. Not that I didn't believe in you. I mean, I put down twenty against both Venkman and Winston that you'd... live. But the way you have this park running, well, that's almost as cool as memorizing Tobin's Spirit Guide.
